---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Participant Handbook — Explore China" lang="en" alternateHref="/zh/handbook" alternateLabel="中文" darkNav={true}>

  <div class="handbook-page">

    <!-- 1. Page Header -->
    <header class="handbook-header">
      <p class="handbook-header__eyebrow">Explore China 2026</p>
      <h1 class="handbook-header__title">Participant Handbook</h1>
      <p class="handbook-header__sub">Everything you need before departure — in one page.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Section Nav -->
    <nav class="handbook-nav" aria-label="Handbook sections">
      <p class="handbook-nav__label">Jump to section</p>
      <ul class="handbook-nav__list">
        <li><a href="#checklist">Pre-Departure Checklist</a></li>
        <li><a href="#entry">Entry Requirements</a></li>
        <li><a href="#vpn">VPN</a></li>
        <li><a href="#sim">SIM &amp; Internet</a></li>
        <li><a href="#apps">Apps &amp; Payment</a></li>
        <li><a href="#packing">Packing</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <!-- Critical Warning — one place only -->
    <div class="handbook-callout">
      <p><strong>⚠ Two critical rules:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Install your VPN before you board.</strong> It cannot be downloaded inside China.</li>
        <li><strong>Turn VPN OFF when setting up Alipay / WeChat Pay.</strong> Verification will fail otherwise.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <!-- 2. Quick Checklist -->
    <section id="checklist" class="handbook-section">
      <h2>Pre-Departure Checklist</h2>
      <ul class="handbook-checklist">
        <li><span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span><span>Passport valid for 6+ months beyond travel dates</span></li>
        <li><span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span><span>Hotel booking + return flight booked (required for entry)</span></li>
        <li><span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span><span>VPN installed and tested</span></li>
        <li><span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span><span>WeChat downloaded — account verified — Visa/Mastercard linked</span></li>
        <li><span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span><span>Alipay downloaded — passport verified — Visa/Mastercard linked</span></li>
        <li><span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span><span>DiDi downloaded</span></li>
        <li><span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span><span>SIM / eSIM sorted</span></li>
        <li><span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span><span>Some cash (RMB) — foreign cards occasionally declined at small vendors</span></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- 3. Entry Requirements -->
    <section id="entry" class="handbook-section">
      <h2>Entry Requirements</h2>
      <p><strong>Canadian &amp; UK passport holders:</strong> visa-free for up to 30 days (valid until Dec 31, 2026).</p>
      <p><strong>Other passports:</strong> may qualify for 240-hour visa-free transit — verify before booking.</p>

      <p class="handbook-label">You need at the border:</p>
      <ul class="handbook-list">
        <li>Passport (6+ months validity)</li>
        <li>Confirmed hotel booking</li>
        <li>Return/onward flight ticket</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="handbook-links">
        <a class="handbook-link" href="https://ca.china-embassy.gov.cn/eng/zytz_0/202602/t20260216_11860601.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Official visa-free policy notice (Chinese Embassy in Canada)</a>
        <a class="handbook-link" href="https://www.fmprc.gov.cn/eng/xw/fyrbt/202602/t20260215_11860467.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MFA announcement — Canada &amp; UK visa-free entry</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. VPN -->
    <section id="vpn" class="handbook-section">
      <h2>VPN</h2>
      <p>Google, Instagram, WhatsApp, YouTube are all blocked in China. Your VPN must be installed and working <strong>before you board your flight</strong>.</p>

      <div class="handbook-links">
        <a class="handbook-link" href="https://www.expressvpn.com/order" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ExpressVPN — sign up &amp; download</a>
        <a class="handbook-link" href="https://nordvpn.com/pricing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NordVPN — plans &amp; download</a>
        <a class="handbook-link" href="https://www.astrill.com/pricing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astrill — sign up (popular among expats in China)</a>
      </div>

      <p class="handbook-note">Pro tip: eSIMs from providers like Holafly or Airalo route traffic through overseas servers — some users report Google/WhatsApp working without a VPN. But still install one as backup.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 5. SIM & Internet -->
    <section id="sim" class="handbook-section">
      <h2>SIM &amp; Internet</h2>
      <p>You need data for WeChat Pay, DiDi, maps, and everything else. Three options:</p>

      <div class="handbook-sim-cards">
        <div class="handbook-sim-card">
          <span class="badge-recommended">Recommended</span>
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__name">eSIM</div>
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__desc">Set up before you fly. No physical SIM swap. Some eSIMs bypass the firewall (no VPN needed for Google/WhatsApp). Downside: no Chinese phone number.</div>
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__links">
            <a class="handbook-link" href="https://www.holafly.com/esim-china" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Holafly — China eSIM (unlimited data)</a>
            <a class="handbook-link" href="https://www.airalo.com/china" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Airalo — China eSIM plans</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="handbook-sim-card">
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__name">Local Chinese SIM</div>
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__desc">Best for app verification and ride-hailing (Chinese phone number). Buy at the airport on arrival. Need VPN for Google/WhatsApp.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="handbook-sim-card">
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__name">Roaming</div>
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__desc">Easiest — just turn on roaming with your Canadian carrier. Usually bypasses the firewall. Expensive for heavy use.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 6. Apps & Payment -->
    <section id="apps" class="handbook-section">
      <h2>Apps &amp; Payment</h2>
      <p>Three essential apps. Download and set up <strong>before you land</strong>. Turn VPN off during setup.</p>

      <div class="handbook-app-cards">
        <div class="handbook-app-card">
          <div class="handbook-app-card__icon">💬</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__name">WeChat</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__desc">Chat + payment + group comms for the program.</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__setup">
            <p class="setup-label">Setup:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Register with your phone number</li>
              <li>Go to Me → Settings → verify identity with passport</li>
              <li>Me → Services → Wallet → link Visa or Mastercard</li>
            </ol>
            <div class="handbook-sim-card__links">
              <a class="handbook-link" href="https://help.wechat.com/cgi-bin/micromsg-bin/oshelpcenter?opcode=2&id=2307252mur7f2307257zfyfe&lang=en&plat=ios&Channel=helpcenter" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Official: Link international card to WeChat Pay</a>
              <a class="handbook-link" href="https://www.trip.com/guide/phone/wechat-pay-for-foreigners.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Step-by-step guide with screenshots (Trip.com)</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="handbook-app-card">
          <div class="handbook-app-card__icon">💳</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__name">Alipay</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__desc">Primary payment at shops, restaurants, and transit.</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__setup">
            <p class="setup-label">Setup:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Register with your phone number</li>
              <li>Complete identity verification with passport</li>
              <li>Link Visa or Mastercard (credit card works — debit may not)</li>
            </ol>
            <div class="handbook-sim-card__links">
              <a class="handbook-link" href="https://us.trip.com/blog/how-to-use-alipay-with-a-foreign-credit-card/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Step-by-step: Alipay with foreign card (Trip.com)</a>
              <a class="handbook-link" href="https://www.travelofchina.com/alipay-setup-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alipay setup guide for foreigners 2026</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="handbook-app-card">
          <div class="handbook-app-card__icon">🚗</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__name">DiDi</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__desc">Ride-hailing (China's Uber). Pay through Alipay or linked card.</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__setup">
            <p class="setup-label">Setup:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Download DiDi from your app store</li>
              <li>Register with phone number</li>
              <li>Settings → Language → English</li>
              <li>Link Alipay as payment method (or add card directly)</li>
            </ol>
            <div class="handbook-sim-card__links">
              <a class="handbook-link" href="https://www.trip.com/guide/transport/how-to-use-didi-in-china.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">How to use DiDi in China (Trip.com guide)</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="handbook-note">P2P transfers (sending money to friends) are usually restricted for foreign cards. Bring some RMB cash as backup for small vendors.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 7. Packing -->
    <section id="packing" class="handbook-section handbook-section--stub">
      <h2>Packing, Transport, Health &amp; Emergency</h2>
      <div class="stub-box">
        <span class="stub-icon">🔜</span>
        <p>These sections are being prepared. Details will be added closer to departure.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

</Layout>

<style>
  .handbook-callout {
    max-width: 52rem;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: #fef3c7;
    border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #78350f;
  }
  .handbook-callout ol {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }
  .handbook-callout li {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .handbook-label {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #78716c;
    margin: 1rem 0 0.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .handbook-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #44403c;
  }
  .handbook-list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .handbook-sim-card__links {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }
  .handbook-app-card__setup {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #e7e5e4;
  }
  .handbook-app-card__setup .setup-label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #78716c;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .handbook-app-card__setup ol {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #57534e;
  }
  .handbook-app-card__setup ol li {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .handbook-app-card__setup .handbook-link {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
</style>
